OL,3,CUK Government's veto of Scotland's
OL,4,Cgender reform bill was legal, court
OL,5,Crules
OL,7,FA judge has ruled the UK was acting
OL,8,Flegally when it blocked reforms in
OL,9,FScotland to make it easier for
OL,10,Ftransgender people to change sex.
OL,12,FWestminster used a never-before-used
OL,13,Flegislation last year to prevent
OL,14,FScotland's Gender Recognition Reform
OL,15,FBill from becoming law.
OL,17,FIt would have simplified the process
OL,18,Ffor transgender people to get a Gender
OL,19,FRecognition Certificate (GRC), thereby
OL,20,Fofficially changing their legally-
OL,21,Frecognised sex.
